020package org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer;
021
022import static org.apiguardian.api.API.Status.STABLE;
023import static org.tquadrat.foundation.lang.Objects.requireNonNullArgument;
024
025import javax.lang.model.element.TypeParameterElement;
026import javax.lang.model.type.TypeVariable;
027import java.lang.reflect.Type;
028import java.util.List;
029
030import org.apiguardian.api.API;
031import org.tquadrat.foundation.annotation.ClassVersion;
032import org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.internal.TypeVariableNameImpl;
033
034/**
035 *  The specialisation of
036 *  {@link TypeName}
037 *  for type variable names.
038 *
039 *  @author Square,Inc.
040 *  @modified Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
041 *  @version $Id: TypeVariableName.java 1085 2024-01-05 16:23:28Z tquadrat $
042 *  @since 0.0.5
043 *
044 *  @UMLGraph.link
045 */
046@ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: TypeVariableName.java 1085 2024-01-05 16:23:28Z tquadrat $" )
047@API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
048public sealed interface TypeVariableName extends TypeName
049    permits TypeVariableNameImpl
050{
051        /*---------*\
052    ====** Methods **==========================================================
053        \*---------*/
054    /**
055     *  {@inheritDoc}
056     */
057    @Override
058    public TypeVariableName annotated( final List<AnnotationSpec> annotations );
059
060    /**
061     *  Returns type variable equivalent to the given type.
062     *
063     *  @param  type    The type.
064     *  @return The type variable name.
065     */
066    @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
067    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
068    public static TypeVariableName from( final java.lang.reflect.TypeVariable<?> type )
069    {
070        final var retValue = TypeVariableNameImpl.from( type );
071
072        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
073        return retValue;
074    }   //  from()
075
076    /**
077     *  Returns a new type variable named {@code name} without bounds.
078     *
079     *  @param  name    The name.
080     *  @return The type variable name.
081     */
082    @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
083    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
084    public static TypeVariableName from( final String name )
085    {
086        final var retValue = TypeVariableNameImpl.from( name );
087
088        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
089        return retValue;
090    }   //  from()
091
092    /**
093     *  Returns a new type variable named {@code name} with {@code bounds}.
094     *
095     *  @param  name    The name.
096     *  @param  bounds  The bounds.
097     *  @return The type variable name.
098     */
099    @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
100    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
101    public static TypeVariableName from( final String name, final Type... bounds )
102    {
103        final var retValue = TypeVariableNameImpl.from( name, bounds );
104
105        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
106        return retValue;
107    }   //  from()
108
109    /**
110     *  Returns a new type variable named {@code name} with {@code bounds}.
111     *
112     *  @param  name    The name.
113     *  @param  bounds  The bounds.
114     *  @return The type variable name.
115     */
116    @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
117    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
118    public static TypeVariableName from( final String name, final TypeName... bounds )
119    {
120        final var retValue = TypeVariableNameImpl.from( name, bounds );
121
122        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
123        return retValue;
124    }   //  from()
125
126    /**
127     *  Returns a type variable name that is equivalent to the given element.
128     *
129     *  @param  element The element.
130     *  @return The new type variable name.
131     */
132    @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
133    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
134    public static TypeVariableName from( final TypeParameterElement element )
135    {
136        final var retValue = TypeVariableNameImpl.from( element );
137
138        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
139        return retValue;
140    }   //  from()
141
142    /**
143     *  Returns a type variable name that is equivalent to the given mirror.
144     *
145     *  @param  mirror  The mirror.
146     *  @return The new type variable name.
147     */
148    @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
149    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
150    public static TypeVariableName from( final TypeVariable mirror )
151    {
152        final var retValue = TypeVariableNameImpl.from( (TypeParameterElement) requireNonNullArgument( mirror, "mirror" ).asElement() );
153
154        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
155        return retValue;
156    }   //  from()
157
158    /**
159     *  Returns a new instance for an implementation of
160     *  {@code TypeVariableName} as a copy of this one, but with the given
161     *  bounds added.
162     *
163     *  @param  bounds  The additional bounds.
164     *  @return The new type variable name.
165     */
166    public TypeVariableName withBounds( final List<TypeName> bounds );
167
168    /**
169     *  Returns a new instance for an implementation of
170     *  {@code TypeVariableName} as a copy of this one, but with the given
171     *  bounds added.
172     *
173     *  @param  bounds  The additional bounds.
174     *  @return The new type variable name.
175     */
176    public TypeVariableName withBounds( final Type... bounds );
177
178    /**
179     *  Returns a new instance for an implementation of
180     *  {@code TypeVariableName} as a copy of this one, but with the given
181     *  bounds added.
182     *
183     *  @param  bounds  The additional bounds.
184     *  @return The new type variable name.
185     */
186    public TypeVariableName withBounds( final TypeName... bounds );
187
188    /**
189     *  {@inheritDoc}
190     */
191    @Override
192    public TypeName withoutAnnotations();
193}
194//  interface TypeVariableName
195
